verbose_text: To examine whether the modest difference in wound re-epithelialization between WT and efnB1 Deltaepi mice was a consequence of redundancy across the ephrin-B ligands, we wounded epidermis specific, double ephrin-B1 and -B2 KO mice (efnB1/B2 Deltaepi), which tissue biopsies indicated to have considerably reduced levels of efnB1 and B2 mRNA (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY F and S4G).
